# VITAL: Ask MilePilot Production (MP-S5 — LOCKED)

**Ask MilePilot is an accepted production feature.** PR #163 merged; MP-S5-005 audit approved.

## Rules for agents and developers

1. **Visual shell** (`ask-milepilot-view.js`) — do NOT change typography, spacing, colours, composer layout, or confirmation UI without MP-S4 visual sign-off.
2. **Intent registry** — all routing changes go through `IntentRouter`; add tests for collisions (email lookup vs email action, claim vs mileage, report vs trips).
3. **Action execution** — external actions (prepare/export/email) require confirmation flow; never execute on `handleQuestion`.
4. **Financial answers** — must use `MPTaxEngine` only; no `miles × rate` or stored `hmrc` sums. See ADR 001.
5. **Not-connected features** — fuel, VAT, accountant pack return `NotConnected` until Business Workspace data sources exist.
6. **Missing email** — block email action preparation; direct user to Settings; no fake recipients.
7. Before intentional changes: run `npm run test:ask-milepilot`, `npm run test:ask-parity`, and `npm run test:vital`.

## Protected subsystems

| Subsystem | File | Review trigger |
|-----------|------|----------------|
| Visual shell | `ask-milepilot-view.js` | Any CSS class / layout change |
| Intent registry | `IntentRouter` in service | New intent, regex change, collision fix |
| Action executor | `ActionExecutor` | Confirm/cancel/execute flow |
| Lifecycle | `ask-milepilot-app.js` | mount/leave, listener binding |
| Production routing | `index.html` Ask wiring | showAsk, deep link, session restore |

